- Install Redis using `sudo apt-get install redis-server` on Ubuntu.
- Use `npm install express redis` to add Express and Redis packages.
- Configure Redis client in your app with:
  ```javascript
  const redis = require('redis');
  const client = redis.createClient();
  ```
- Implement caching middleware:
  ```javascript
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    const key = req.originalUrl;
    client.get(key, (err, reply) => {
      if (reply !== null) {
        res.send(reply);
      } else {
        res.on('finish', () => {
          client.setex(key, 3600, res.body); // Cache for 1 hour
        });
        next();
      }
    });
  });
  ```
- Use `client.setex` to set cache with expiration time.
- Monitor Redis performance using `redis-cli --stat`.
- Update Express and Redis packages regularly:
  ```bash
  npm update express redis
  ```
